            <h2>2. Accuracy</h2>
        </div>

        <h3>2.1 Does the AI Do What It Claims to Do?</h3>
        <p>
            Yes. TalkScore uses advanced speech recognition and <strong>machine learning models trained on human examiners' ratings</strong> to evaluate spoken English. The system has been designed and validated to produce scores that closely match what a professional human evaluator would give. Key accuracy characteristics:
        </p>

        <div class="finding">
            <div class="finding-stat">5</div>
            <div class="finding-text">
                <h5>Independent Language Dimensions Assessed</h5>
                <p>Pronunciation, Fluency, Grammar, Vocabulary, and Coherence are each evaluated using specialized AI models ‚Äî no dimension is used as a proxy for another.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="finding">
            <div class="finding-stat">0‚Äì100</div>
            <div class="finding-text">
                <h5>Granular Pronunciation Scoring</h5>
                <p>Every word and phoneme receives an individual quality score (0‚Äì100), with 90+ indicating native or near-native pronunciation. Accents are not penalized unless they affect intelligibility.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="finding">
            <div class="finding-stat">ML</div>
            <div class="finding-text">
                <h5>Trained on Human Examiner Ratings</h5>
                <p>Scoring algorithms were trained on large datasets of native and non-native speakers rated by human examiners, ensuring outputs correlate with expert judgment rather than simple rule-based deductions.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <h3>2.2 FAQ Answers Accuracy</h3>
        <p>
            FAQ responses are validated through the same multi-stage QA process as all AI agent capabilities. During the pre-deployment phase, FAQ accuracy is tested extensively. Post-deployment, every conversation is monitored for <code>hallucination</code> flags ‚Äî detecting when the AI provides false, incorrect, or fabricated information ‚Äî and <code>vague_answers</code> flags ‚Äî detecting incomplete or non-specific responses. These flags trigger immediate alerts and prompt corrections.
        </p>

        <h3>2.3 TalkScore Results Accuracy</h3>
        <p>
            TalkScore evaluates candidates across two independent tracks ‚Äî <strong>language proficiency</strong> and <strong>soft skills</strong> ‚Äî each assessed through dedicated AI models:
        </p>

        <h4>Language Assessment (5 dimensions)</h4>
