        <div class="info-box green">
            <h5>Independent Assessment Tracks</h5>
            <p>Language proficiency and soft skills are assessed through <strong>separate, dedicated AI models</strong>. A candidate's grammar score does not influence their customer service orientation score, and vice versa. Each dimension is evaluated on its own merits, ensuring no cross-contamination between assessment tracks.</p>
        </div>

        <h3>2.4 Voice AI Captured Attributes</h3>
        <p>
            All captured attributes ‚Äî scores, answers, evaluation flags ‚Äî undergo the same dual validation process:
        </p>
        <ol style="padding-left: 20px; margin: 15px 0;">
            <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;"><strong>Pre-deployment validation:</strong> Manually tested multiple times by internal QA teams plus 100+ automated test calls with diverse AI candidate profiles.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;"><strong>Post-deployment monitoring:</strong> Every call is captured, analyzed, and checked for information being missed or errors in attribute capture. Discrepancies are visible through internal dashboards.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>2.5 Job Matching / Lead Scoring</h3>
        <p>
            Scoring is driven by the composite AI Interview Score, which integrates both language and behavioral signals. The composite score is designed to appropriately weight both language proficiency and behavioral competencies based on the requirements of each role. The holistic scoring model ‚Äî trained on human examiner ratings ‚Äî considers all dimensions together rather than applying fixed formulaic weights, reflecting how professional evaluators assess overall candidate quality.
        </p>
    </div>

